  "subject": "Failed to deploy so artifacts in nexus (again)",
  "commit_message": "Failed to deploy so artifacts in nexus (again)\n\nThere are Linux Foundation rules (enforced by nexus) that I still\ndon't really understand.\n\nI'm convinced this is absolutely true:\n\nThe groupId of every artifact in a project MUST begin with:\n\torg.openecomp.<project>\n\t   --or--\n\torg.onap.<project>\n\nThe top-level artifact is no exception.  So for example, this is\nNOT allowed:\n\n\t<groupId>org.openecomp</groupId>\n\t<artifactId>so</groupId>\n\nI'm not so sure about this:\n\nThe artifactId in the top level pom must match the project name,\nso for \"so\", the artifact MUST be:\n\n\t<groupId>org.openecomp.so</groupId>\n\t<artifactId>so</groupId>\n\nConsequently, the path to the top level \"so\" artifact will be:\n\n\torg/openecomp/so/so/1.1.0-SNAPSHOT/so-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT.pom\n\nIt seems rather unfortunate to have \"/so/so/\" in the path.  Perhaps\nthe \"so\" project repositories could be restructured to be more like\nother projects', but this time, it's impractical.\n\nIssue: SO-21\nChange-Id: Id74cdc4fd47bda1d1ec5aff1d01726891f544e06\nSigned-off-by: Rob Daugherty <rd472p@att.com>\n",
